                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām Mariham ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus kahāli ... "O my Lady Mary, Mother of Jesus the Almighty ..." (fol. 6ra-rb) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fol. 6rb-6vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are numbered. The 34th miracle has erroneously been given number 35.</note>
                     <note>The first two miracles and miracle 57 are followed by a short hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām za-ǝnbälä zärʾa bǝʾǝsi za-wälädkiyo la-ʾamlāk ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary without seed of a man who conceived by God ..." (fols. 10vb-11ra)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ṣǝwwaʿa lǝbbuna malakotāwi ... "O my Lady, Virgin Mary call of the divine comprehension ..." (fol. 13ra)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ... "O my Lady, Virgin Mary, for Nicodemus, fighter against many sins and transgressions ..." (fol. 85rb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>A short supplication is written before the last miracle:</note>
                     <note>- ነዋ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ እጽሕፍ፡ ተአምሪኪ፡ ... (fol. 90rb)</note>
                  </msItem>
